y bathroom vanity which are classic Edison bulbs. The issues I have with the real ones now are the kelvin color output, the wattage and the heat they generate.</p>\n<p>Since there is no window or ventilation flow, the heat they generate was the driving factor to find CFL&#8217;s or the better LED bulb. The only downside I saw was the look of the bulbs in the glass fixtures.</p>\n<p>After a quick look for a brighter white and/or wattage with medium range lumens around 500. I came across these <a href=\"http://amzn.com/B00HZC5UOW?tag=thefro-20\">LED Filament A19 4W</a> replacements on Amazon for only ~$10. Bought two and am real happy so far.</p>\n<p>Let me know what you think of the bulbs.</p>\n\n<a href=\'http://austin.passy.co/2014/led-filament-bulbs/20140528-211457-76497991-jpg/\'><img width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" src=\"http://i0.wp.com/austin.passy.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/05/20140528-211457-76497991.jpg?resize=1024%2C768\" class=\"attachment-large size-large\" alt=\"LED Filament Bulb plugged in\" srcset=\"http://i0.wp.com/austin.passy.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/05/20140528-211457-76497991.jpg?resize=300%2C225 300w, http://i0.wp.com/austin.passy.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/05/20140528-211457-76497991.jpg?resize=175%2C131 175w, http://i0.wp.com/austin.passy.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/05/20140528-211457-76497991.jpg?resize=666%2C500 666w, http://i0.wp.com/austin.passy.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/05/20140528-211457-76497991.jpg?w=1024 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" data-attachment-id=\"2893\" data-orig-file=\"http://i0.wp.com/austin.passy.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/05/20140528-211457-76497991.jpg?resize=1024%2C768\" data-orig-size=\"1024,768\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;2.4&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;1401306458&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&qu