8217;ve been following some great posts and UX trends about checkout page design. So I recently spend the day modifying the checkout page of my Premium WordPress plugin site <a href=\"http://extendd.com/\">Extendd</a>.</p>\n<p>I also recently moved <a href=\"http://extendd.com/\">Extendd</a> to <a href=\"http://frosty.me/extendd-pagely\">Pagely</a> and added SSL support again to re-implement Stripe payments (Credit Cards).</p>\n<p>My checkout page improvements we&#8217;re helped in part by <a href=\"https://yoast.com/checkout-page-improvements/\">Yoast&#8217;s</a> posts and this <a href=\"http://uxmovement.com/forms/why-users-fill-out-less-if-you-mark-required-fields/\">UX Movement</a> post.</p>\n<h3>The Checkout page</h3>\n<p><strong>Before</strong><br />\n<a href=\"http://i2.wp.com/austin.passy.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/05/extendd-checkout-before.png\"><img src=\"http://i2.wp.com/austin.passy.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/05/extendd-checkout-before.png?resize=416%2C1024\" alt=\"Extendd.com Checkout Page Before\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-2879\" srcset=\"http://i2.wp.com/austin.passy.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/05/extendd-checkout-before.png?resize=416%2C1024 416w, http://i2.wp.com/austin.passy.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/05/extendd-checkout-before.png?resize=203%2C500 203w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 416px) 100vw, 416px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>After</strong><br />\n<a href=\"http://i0.wp.com/austin.passy.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/05/extendd-checkout-after.png\"><img src=\"http://i0.wp.com/austin.passy.co/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/05/extendd-checkout-after.png?resize=421%2C1024\" alt=\"Extendd.com Checkout Page After\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-2880\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /></a></p>\n<p>Let me know what you think of the new design.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AustinPassy/~4/E-daclxUoaU\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base